    {
      "citation_id": "[CITATION_1]",
      "span_text": "TCZ is a recombinant humanized anti-IL-6 receptor monoclonal antibody, administered monthly by intravenous infusion (IV) that prevents IL-6 signal transduction ( Figure 2). By binding selectively and competitively to both mIL-6R and sIL-6R, TCZ prevents the dimerization of gp130 on the cell membrane and therefore blocks the pro-inflammatory effects of IL-6. Furthermore, TCZ has the capacity to dissociate IL-6/IL-6R complexes that have already formed. TCZ is approved in Europe and the United States for the treatment of moderate to severe RA in adult patients who have responded inadequately or have been intolerant to previous therapy with one or more DMARDs or TNF inhibitors."
